This paper deals with deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses neural architecture search (NAS) techniques, which fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves optimization and computational complexity, which are relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
